"https://lobste.rs/s/y0tvll","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/y0tvll/jim_s_truetype_qr_code_font"},{"short_id":"44nzhz","created_at":"2026-07-07T22:19:39.000-05:00","title":"Computational Balloon Twisting: The Theory of Balloon Polyhedra (2008)","url":"https://cccg.ca/proceedings/2008/paper34full.pdf","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"\u003cp\u003eThis paper builds a general mathematical and algorithmic theory for balloon-twisting structures,\nfrom balloon animals to balloon polyhedra, by modeling their underlying graphs (edge skeleta). In\nparticular, we give algorithms to find the fewest balloons that can make exactly a desired graph or, using\nfewer balloons but allowing repeated traversal or shortcuts, the minimum total length needed by a given\nnumber of balloons. In contrast, we show NP-completeness of determining whether such an optimal\nconstruction is possible with balloons of equal length.\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"This paper builds a general mathematical and algorithmic theory for balloon-twisting structures,\r\nfrom balloon animals to balloon polyhedra, by modeling their underlying graphs (edge skeleta). In\r\nparticular, we give algorithms to find the fewest balloons that can make exactly a desired graph or, using\r\nfewer balloons but allowing repeated traversal or shortcuts, the minimum total length needed by a given\r\nnumber of balloons. In contrast, we show NP-completeness of determining whether such an optimal\r\nconstruction is possible with balloons of equal length.","submitter_user":"fanf","user_is_author":false,"tags":["math","pdf"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/44nzhz","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/44nzhz/computational_balloon_twisting_theory"},{"short_id":"gdtd9v","created_at":"2026-07-07T21:34:02.000-05:00","title":"Unplatform From The Superhighway","url":"https://unplatform.fromthesuperhighway.com/","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"